{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review (T10 Infrastructure/IaC overlay): **NOT-APPLICABLE — no findings.**\n\nThis plan is a pure application-software deliverable: a Python diff context-assembler (`src/rebar/llm/code_review/assemble.py`), a Markdown/front-matter prompt file (`src/rebar/llm/reviewers/code-review-base.md`), and a JSON schema registration in `src/rebar/schemas/`. No infrastructure is provisioned or configured — no Terraform/CloudFormation/CDK/Pulumi/Ansible, no Kubernetes/Helm, no cloud resource creation. The AWS-hosted Gerrit environment referenced by the parent epic (b744) is gated on a separate ticket (`d251`) and is explicitly **out of scope** for WS1. The T10 overlay does not apply; all T10 sub-checks (remote state, IAM, idempotency, blast radius, secrets-in-IaC, cost/sizing, observability-for-infra) are not triggered. No T10 findings."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782620991998151001,"uuid":"f0fecf5c-8a74-4550-896d-0fa4f2dbab4a"}